{
  "_schema": "tonight.artists/1",
  "_readme": [
    "Optional enrichment lookup for performers. The front end fuzzy-matches an",
    "event to an artist here to show the band website and a real photo when the",
    "venue feed has none (e.g. McCarthy's / Toad placeholder images).",
    "Matching: normalize (lowercase, strip punctuation and a leading 'the') the",
    "performer name derived from the event title, then compare against name and",
    "alt_names. Add alt_names for spelling/formatting variants so fuzzy matches",
    "land.",
    "To enrich an act: fill in website and/or image_url. Leave nulls otherwise —",
    "a null field just means 'no override'. Adding an artist here never creates",
    "events; it only decorates events that already exist. This file is hand-",
    "maintained; the scraper never writes it (same contract as data/venues.json)."
  ],
  "_fields": {
    "name": "canonical display name (string)",
    "alt_names": "array of alternate spellings/aliases for fuzzy matching",
    "website": "official site or primary social page URL, or null",
    "image_url": "direct URL to a band photo / promo image, or null",
    "notes": "freeform (genre, home stage, etc.), or null",
    "titles": "optional array of EXACT event titles that always map here — highest priority, the way to correct a wrong auto-match (e.g. when a quoted series name outranks the real performer)",
    "match_contains": "optional array of substrings; matches any title containing one — LOWEST priority, for house/generic images like a shared 'Irish Session' photo. Specific artists still win."
  },
